social_posts.post_text:
The most joyous thing I’ve done this season was get smacked in the face by the intense aroma of ginger walking into @omnigrovepark’s 30th National Gingerbread House Competition !!! 

It was an honor to be a first time judge this year alongside the incredible OG judges. A competition I’ve admired from afar since I was a youngin’. 

There were gingerbread clays and gingerbread leathers, nori sheets for windows, rosemary for blades of grass and weeping willows of celery string. The creativity was on overload 🤯. 
The “gingerbread heads” (my new name for participants) are a wildly talented bunch. Here are just some of my faves out of the 200+ submissions this year😳

The truf plug @wildwildgood came through with a fresh batch of Imaia Gigantea the other day so we shaved these aromatic babes over bucatini with red eye gravy. 
Fun fact: these v rare truffles have only been found in our Appalachian Mountains and Japan🙃

Letting this moment live on the feed so I can remember that it ACTUALLY happened😆

A few days ago I was invited to visit the @whitehouse along with 80 other distinguished food pros for the launch of the  #DiplimaticCulinaryPartnship in conjunction with @statedept and @beardfoundation

I’m jazzed about collaborating with such an intellectual group of world changers as a member of the American Culinary Corps 🇺🇸

9.18 | GOOD HOT FISH X MR. TUNA

Ashleigh Shanti is coming to town! Join us for a collaborative dinner with @foodordeath_ of @goodhotfish & @jordan__rubin of @mr.tuna_maine for a tasting menu highlighting (mostly) New England seafood with southern flavors. Hosted at Bar Futo September 18th 5-9pm.

Ashleigh Shanti is a North Carolina-based chef specializing in Southern cuisine, specific to the Appalachian region. In 2020, Ashleigh was a finalist for the James Beard “Rising Star Chef of the Year” award and during her tenure as Chef de Cuisine at Benne on Eagle, led the establishment to Bon Appetit’s and Thrillist's 2020 Best New Restaurants lists. In 2022, Ashleigh competed on Top Chef: Houston, making it far in the competition representing multi-regional Southern foodways. Currently, Ashleigh is opening Good Hot Fish, a fast casual modern day fish camp in Asheville, NC.
